30|$|Three {{distinct}} elements {{have been taken}} into consideration in the modelling phase. These elements are topology, interlocking table and train motion. While the topology model includes the states and positions of the <b>blocks,</b> points and <b>signals,</b> the <b>interlocking</b> table model comprises the basic requirements for opening all the possible routes. On the other hand, the train motion model represents the vehicle movement according to the signalization system.|$|R
