5|$|The system {{currently}} uses Automatic <b>Block</b> <b>Signaling</b> with fixed wayside {{signals and}} automatic train stops {{in order to}} provide safe train operation across the whole system. The New York City Subway system has, for the most part, used <b>block</b> <b>signalling</b> since its 1904 opening, and many portions of the signaling system were installed between the 1930s and 1960s.|$|R
